30|$|The Rawalpindi train yard has ten {{platforms}} in total. Five platforms {{are reserved}} for passengers while the rest are for goods. Due to the decline in railway operations, only the <b>passenger</b> <b>platforms</b> have remained operational. Furthermore, only the <b>passenger</b> <b>platforms</b> and their lines have a track detection circuit installed. This station is equipped with warner, home, starter, advance starter, shunting and outer signals (Satish and Agarwal 2007).|$|R
