50|$|Melton station {{opened on}} 2 April 1884, when {{the line from}} Braybrook Junction opened. The line was {{extended}} westward to Parwan station in 1886, and being on a single track section of track, the station served as a crossing loop from this time. By 1889 the station had an interlocked signal box, single <b>passenger</b> <b>platform,</b> and a three road yard. A goods shed also existed across from the <b>passenger</b> <b>platform.</b>|$|R
